<p>I can't seems to find solution to create multi-column / magazine layout using <code>HTML</code> and <code>CSS</code> keeping cross browser compatibility in mind. Don't really want to heavily relay on JavaScript for layout.</p>  <p>Here I've attached wire-frame for what I'm about to got with: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/BUeJs.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/BUeJs.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Although it's simple two column layout template; I would like to pull small block (image + text block) dynamically with client side template. Hence <strong>structure for all 10 blocks have to be identical and will flow automatically as multi-column magazine layout</strong> starting after bigger text container and will end as shown in wire-frame.</p>  <p>I had hard time getting it as expected; tried <code>column-count</code>, <code>column-width</code>, <code>column-span</code> etc. all fancy looking CSS3 proerties but doesn't look they work as expected cross browser. Layout fall flat when it comes to <code>column-span</code> which doesn't have support in Firefox.</p>  <p><div class="snippet" data-lang="js" data-hide="true"> <div class="snippet-code snippet-currently-hidden"> <pre class="snippet-code-css lang-css prettyprint-override"><code>.b-box {   width: 250px; } .b-box li {   border: 1px solid #E7E7E7;   display: block;   clear: both;   overflow: auto;   margin-bottom: 5px; } .b-box li:after {   height: 0;   clear: both; } .b-box li img {   width: 50px;   height: 50px;   float: left;   margin: 5px 10px 5px 5px; } .b-box li a {}</code></pre> <pre class="snippet-code-html lang-html prettyprint-override"><code>&lt;ul class="b-box"&gt;   &lt;li&gt;     &lt;img src="xyz.jpg" alt="Image XYZ" /&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr   &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;     &lt;img src="xyz.jpg" alt="Image XYZ" /&gt;Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consetetur sadipscing elitr   &lt;/li&gt;   &lt;li&gt;     &lt;img src="xyz.j